FBIS4-17146 "drsov077_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Grachev To Brief NATO Officials on Partnership Stance Grachev To Brief NATO Officials on Partnership Stance LD2004170794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1556 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004170794 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Andrey Palaria and Sergey Ostanin] [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS--Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev will visit Brussels on May 25-26 to inform NATO officials about Russia's position on the Partnership for Peace programme. Following recent NATO air strikes in Bosnia, the Russian Defence Ministry "has slightly reviewed its stand on the matter, taking into account the position Russia holds in Europe and in the rest of the world," Grachev said. Speaking at a meeting with visiting Turkish Defence Minister Mehmet Golhan in Moscow on Wednesday, Grachev said that during his visit to Brussels he will also brief the defence ministers of NATO and other countries on the key provisions of Russia's military doctrine.
